&lt;p&gt;You spot it the second the sunlight slides across the boards: a faint trough that catches the eye with every step. The room is quiet now—dust settled, stain chosen, plans made—but that shallow divot where the machine paused refuses to disappear. If you’ve ever sanded a hardwood floor, you know this feeling. The drum sander is a capable partner and a stern teacher: get your starts and stops right, or the floor will hold the memory of every hesitation.&lt;/p&gt;</summary><media:content url="https://blog.equalle.com/images/brand/20.webp" medium="image"/><media:content url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2026/02/19/feather-in-starts-and-stops-to-avoid-divots-drum-sander/cards/facebook/feather-in-starts-and-stops-to-avoid-divots-drum-sander.jpg" medium="image"/><media:thumbnail url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2026/02/19/feather-in-starts-and-stops-to-avoid-divots-drum-sander/cards/facebook/feather-in-starts-and-stops-to-avoid-divots-drum-sander.jpg"/><enclosure url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2026/02/19/feather-in-starts-and-stops-to-avoid-divots-drum-sander/cards/facebook/feather-in-starts-and-stops-to-avoid-divots-drum-sander.jpg" type="image/jpeg"/><media:content url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2026/02/19/feather-in-starts-and-stops-to-avoid-divots-drum-sander/cards/instagram/feather-in-starts-and-stops-to-avoid-divots-drum-sander.jpg" medium="image"/><media:thumbnail url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2026/02/19/feather-in-starts-and-stops-to-avoid-divots-drum-sander/cards/instagram/feather-in-starts-and-stops-to-avoid-divots-drum-sander.jpg"/><enclosure url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2026/02/19/feather-in-starts-and-stops-to-avoid-divots-drum-sander/cards/instagram/feather-in-starts-and-stops-to-avoid-divots-drum-sander.jpg" type="image/jpeg"/><media:content url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2026/02/19/feather-in-starts-and-stops-to-avoid-divots-drum-sander/cards/pinterest/feather-in-starts-and-stops-to-avoid-divots-drum-sander.jpg" medium="image"/><media:thumbnail url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2026/02/19/feather-in-starts-and-stops-to-avoid-divots-drum-sander/cards/pinterest/feather-in-starts-and-stops-to-avoid-divots-drum-sander.jpg"/><enclosure url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2026/02/19/feather-in-starts-and-stops-to-avoid-divots-drum-sander/cards/pinterest/feather-in-starts-and-stops-to-avoid-divots-drum-sander.jpg" type="image/jpeg"/><media:content url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2026/02/19/feather-in-starts-and-stops-to-avoid-divots-drum-sander/cards/facebook/feather-in-starts-and-stops-to-avoid-divots-drum-sander.jpg" medium="image"/><media:thumbnail url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2026/02/19/feather-in-starts-and-stops-to-avoid-divots-drum-sander/cards/facebook/feather-in-starts-and-stops-to-avoid-divots-drum-sander.jpg"/><enclosure url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2026/02/19/feather-in-starts-and-stops-to-avoid-divots-drum-sander/cards/facebook/feather-in-starts-and-stops-to-avoid-divots-drum-sander.jpg" type="image/jpeg"/><readingTime>11</readingTime></item><item><title>Set Nails And Countersink Fasteners Before Sanding</title><link>https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2026/02/03/set-nails-and-countersink-fasteners-before-sanding-wood-floor-prep/</link><guid isPermaLink="true">https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2026/02/03/set-nails-and-countersink-fasteners-before-sanding-wood-floor-prep/</guid><pubDate>Tue, 03 Feb 2026 16:06:01 +0000</pubDate><category>Floor &amp; Deck Sanding</category><category>grit-40</category><category>grit-220</category><category>dry sanding</category><description>Make sanding safe and smooth: wood floor prep with nail setting, countersinking, and filling tactics from a pro. Tools, steps, and tips for flawless results.</description><summary>&lt;h2 id="wood-floor-prep-set-nails--countersink-fasteners"&gt;Wood Floor Prep: Set Nails &amp;amp; Countersink Fasteners&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You slide the couch out into the hallway and the room suddenly looks bigger—raw, honest, and ready for a reset. Maybe it’s the house you’ve just moved into. Maybe it’s the living room you’ve ignored for years because the rug hid everything. Either way, today’s the day the floors finally get their turn. You pull on knee pads, switch on a raking work light, and the truth shows up: pings of metal here and there, a few proud fasteners, the dull grin of old staples near the thresholds. It’s not glamorous, but this is the heart of wood floor prep. If you want a glass-smooth finish and belts that don’t shred on first pass, you need every nail set and every screw countersunk—no exceptions.&lt;/p&gt;</summary><media:content url="https://blog.equalle.com/images/brand/04.webp" medium="image"/><media:content url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2026/02/03/set-nails-and-countersink-fasteners-before-sanding-wood-floor-prep/cards/facebook/set-nails-and-countersink-fasteners-before-sanding-wood-floor-prep.jpg" medium="image"/><media:thumbnail url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2026/02/03/set-nails-and-countersink-fasteners-before-sanding-wood-floor-prep/cards/facebook/set-nails-and-countersink-fasteners-before-sanding-wood-floor-prep.jpg"/><enclosure url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2026/02/03/set-nails-and-countersink-fasteners-before-sanding-wood-floor-prep/cards/facebook/set-nails-and-countersink-fasteners-before-sanding-wood-floor-prep.jpg" type="image/jpeg"/><media:content url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2026/02/03/set-nails-and-countersink-fasteners-before-sanding-wood-floor-prep/cards/instagram/set-nails-and-countersink-fasteners-before-sanding-wood-floor-prep.jpg" medium="image"/><media:thumbnail url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2026/02/03/set-nails-and-countersink-fasteners-before-sanding-wood-floor-prep/cards/instagram/set-nails-and-countersink-fasteners-before-sanding-wood-floor-prep.jpg"/><enclosure url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2026/02/03/set-nails-and-countersink-fasteners-before-sanding-wood-floor-prep/cards/instagram/set-nails-and-countersink-fasteners-before-sanding-wood-floor-prep.jpg" type="image/jpeg"/><media:content url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2026/02/03/set-nails-and-countersink-fasteners-before-sanding-wood-floor-prep/cards/pinterest/set-nails-and-countersink-fasteners-before-sanding-wood-floor-prep.jpg" medium="image"/><media:thumbnail url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2026/02/03/set-nails-and-countersink-fasteners-before-sanding-wood-floor-prep/cards/pinterest/set-nails-and-countersink-fasteners-before-sanding-wood-floor-prep.jpg"/><enclosure url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2026/02/03/set-nails-and-countersink-fasteners-before-sanding-wood-floor-prep/cards/pinterest/set-nails-and-countersink-fasteners-before-sanding-wood-floor-prep.jpg" type="image/jpeg"/><media:content url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2026/02/03/set-nails-and-countersink-fasteners-before-sanding-wood-floor-prep/cards/facebook/set-nails-and-countersink-fasteners-before-sanding-wood-floor-prep.jpg" medium="image"/><media:thumbnail url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2026/02/03/set-nails-and-countersink-fasteners-before-sanding-wood-floor-prep/cards/facebook/set-nails-and-countersink-fasteners-before-sanding-wood-floor-prep.jpg"/><enclosure url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2026/02/03/set-nails-and-countersink-fasteners-before-sanding-wood-floor-prep/cards/facebook/set-nails-and-countersink-fasteners-before-sanding-wood-floor-prep.jpg" type="image/jpeg"/><readingTime>11</readingTime></item><item><title>Da Sander Versus Random Orbital For Bodywork Preparation</title><link>https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/12/25/da-sander-versus-random-orbital-for-bodywork-preparation-da-vs-ro-sanding/</link><guid isPermaLink="true">https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/12/25/da-sander-versus-random-orbital-for-bodywork-preparation-da-vs-ro-sanding/</guid><pubDate>Thu, 25 Dec 2025 13:37:54 +0000</pubDate><category>Auto Body Sanding</category><category>grit-40</category><category>grit-80</category><category>grit-120</category><category>grit-150</category><category>grit-180</category><category>grit-220</category><category>grit-320</category><category>grit-400</category><category>grit-600</category><category>orbital sander</category><description>Engineering review of DA vs RO sanding for car bodywork, with test data on removal rates, finish quality, abrasives, and cost to help you prep panels right.</description><summary>&lt;h2 id="da-vs-ro-sanding-for-auto-bodywork-prep"&gt;DA vs RO sanding for Auto Bodywork Prep&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;On a cool Saturday morning, I wheeled a dented fender onto the stand, grabbed coffee, and stared at two sanders: a pneumatic 6-inch “DA” hanging from the air line, and a compact 5-inch corded random orbital sitting on the bench. The car—an aging hatchback—had a blend of bare metal, polyester filler, and feathered edges where clearcoat met primer. This is the exact moment many DIYers and even pros face: DA vs RO sanding for bodywork prep. You’re not choosing a philosophy; you’re choosing a process that affects dust control, scratch depth, shape fidelity, and the time you’ll spend chasing pigtails or re-spraying primer. I’ve felt the allure of the faster-cutting DA when leveling filler, and I’ve also learned the hard way that an aggressive orbit can tunnel through primer on a convex edge in seconds.&lt;/p&gt;</summary><media:content url="https://blog.equalle.com/images/brand/03.webp" medium="image"/><media:content url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/12/25/da-sander-versus-random-orbital-for-bodywork-preparation-da-vs-ro-sanding/cards/facebook/da-sander-versus-random-orbital-for-bodywork-preparation-da-vs-ro-sanding.jpg" medium="image"/><media:thumbnail url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/12/25/da-sander-versus-random-orbital-for-bodywork-preparation-da-vs-ro-sanding/cards/facebook/da-sander-versus-random-orbital-for-bodywork-preparation-da-vs-ro-sanding.jpg"/><enclosure url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/12/25/da-sander-versus-random-orbital-for-bodywork-preparation-da-vs-ro-sanding/cards/facebook/da-sander-versus-random-orbital-for-bodywork-preparation-da-vs-ro-sanding.jpg" type="image/jpeg"/><media:content url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/12/25/da-sander-versus-random-orbital-for-bodywork-preparation-da-vs-ro-sanding/cards/instagram/da-sander-versus-random-orbital-for-bodywork-preparation-da-vs-ro-sanding.jpg" medium="image"/><media:thumbnail url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/12/25/da-sander-versus-random-orbital-for-bodywork-preparation-da-vs-ro-sanding/cards/instagram/da-sander-versus-random-orbital-for-bodywork-preparation-da-vs-ro-sanding.jpg"/><enclosure url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/12/25/da-sander-versus-random-orbital-for-bodywork-preparation-da-vs-ro-sanding/cards/instagram/da-sander-versus-random-orbital-for-bodywork-preparation-da-vs-ro-sanding.jpg" type="image/jpeg"/><media:content url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/12/25/da-sander-versus-random-orbital-for-bodywork-preparation-da-vs-ro-sanding/cards/pinterest/da-sander-versus-random-orbital-for-bodywork-preparation-da-vs-ro-sanding.jpg" medium="image"/><media:thumbnail url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/12/25/da-sander-versus-random-orbital-for-bodywork-preparation-da-vs-ro-sanding/cards/pinterest/da-sander-versus-random-orbital-for-bodywork-preparation-da-vs-ro-sanding.jpg"/><enclosure url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/12/25/da-sander-versus-random-orbital-for-bodywork-preparation-da-vs-ro-sanding/cards/pinterest/da-sander-versus-random-orbital-for-bodywork-preparation-da-vs-ro-sanding.jpg" type="image/jpeg"/><media:content url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/12/25/da-sander-versus-random-orbital-for-bodywork-preparation-da-vs-ro-sanding/cards/facebook/da-sander-versus-random-orbital-for-bodywork-preparation-da-vs-ro-sanding.jpg" medium="image"/><media:thumbnail url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/12/25/da-sander-versus-random-orbital-for-bodywork-preparation-da-vs-ro-sanding/cards/facebook/da-sander-versus-random-orbital-for-bodywork-preparation-da-vs-ro-sanding.jpg"/><enclosure url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/12/25/da-sander-versus-random-orbital-for-bodywork-preparation-da-vs-ro-sanding/cards/facebook/da-sander-versus-random-orbital-for-bodywork-preparation-da-vs-ro-sanding.jpg" type="image/jpeg"/><readingTime>12</readingTime></item><item><title>Edge Sanding Sequence To Match The Drum Sander Scratch</title><link>https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/12/07/edge-sanding-sequence-to-match-the-drum-sander-scratch-edger-sanding/</link><guid isPermaLink="true">https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/12/07/edge-sanding-sequence-to-match-the-drum-sander-scratch-edger-sanding/</guid><pubDate>Sun, 07 Dec 2025 18:13:47 +0000</pubDate><category>Floor &amp; Deck Sanding</category><category>grit-40</category><category>grit-120</category><category>grit-150</category><category>grit-180</category><category>grit progression</category><category>sanding block</category><description>Learn a precise edger sanding sequence to blend edges with drum sander scratches and eliminate halos, swirls, and mismatched textures on hardwood floors.</description><summary>&lt;h2 id="edger-sanding-sequence-to-match-drum-scratches"&gt;Edger sanding sequence to match drum scratches&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The afternoon light slid across your living room, catching the raw promise of bare wood. You’d pulled the last nail out, rented the big-machine sander, and felt that satisfying hum as years of finish lifted away in long, clean passes. The field of the floor looked even—linear, disciplined, almost new. Then your eyes drifted to the perimeter, that six to twelve inches along the baseboards where the drum could never reach. There, the grain looked different. A shadowy ring—soft at first—seemed to appear, like a halo you couldn’t unsee.&lt;/p&gt;</summary><media:content url="https://blog.equalle.com/images/brand/14.webp" medium="image"/><media:content url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/12/07/edge-sanding-sequence-to-match-the-drum-sander-scratch-edger-sanding/cards/facebook/edge-sanding-sequence-to-match-the-drum-sander-scratch-edger-sanding.jpg" medium="image"/><media:thumbnail url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/12/07/edge-sanding-sequence-to-match-the-drum-sander-scratch-edger-sanding/cards/facebook/edge-sanding-sequence-to-match-the-drum-sander-scratch-edger-sanding.jpg"/><enclosure url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/12/07/edge-sanding-sequence-to-match-the-drum-sander-scratch-edger-sanding/cards/facebook/edge-sanding-sequence-to-match-the-drum-sander-scratch-edger-sanding.jpg" type="image/jpeg"/><media:content url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/12/07/edge-sanding-sequence-to-match-the-drum-sander-scratch-edger-sanding/cards/instagram/edge-sanding-sequence-to-match-the-drum-sander-scratch-edger-sanding.jpg" medium="image"/><media:thumbnail url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/12/07/edge-sanding-sequence-to-match-the-drum-sander-scratch-edger-sanding/cards/instagram/edge-sanding-sequence-to-match-the-drum-sander-scratch-edger-sanding.jpg"/><enclosure url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/12/07/edge-sanding-sequence-to-match-the-drum-sander-scratch-edger-sanding/cards/instagram/edge-sanding-sequence-to-match-the-drum-sander-scratch-edger-sanding.jpg" type="image/jpeg"/><media:content url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/12/07/edge-sanding-sequence-to-match-the-drum-sander-scratch-edger-sanding/cards/pinterest/edge-sanding-sequence-to-match-the-drum-sander-scratch-edger-sanding.jpg" medium="image"/><media:thumbnail url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/12/07/edge-sanding-sequence-to-match-the-drum-sander-scratch-edger-sanding/cards/pinterest/edge-sanding-sequence-to-match-the-drum-sander-scratch-edger-sanding.jpg"/><enclosure url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/12/07/edge-sanding-sequence-to-match-the-drum-sander-scratch-edger-sanding/cards/pinterest/edge-sanding-sequence-to-match-the-drum-sander-scratch-edger-sanding.jpg" type="image/jpeg"/><media:content url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/12/07/edge-sanding-sequence-to-match-the-drum-sander-scratch-edger-sanding/cards/facebook/edge-sanding-sequence-to-match-the-drum-sander-scratch-edger-sanding.jpg" medium="image"/><media:thumbnail url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/12/07/edge-sanding-sequence-to-match-the-drum-sander-scratch-edger-sanding/cards/facebook/edge-sanding-sequence-to-match-the-drum-sander-scratch-edger-sanding.jpg"/><enclosure url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/12/07/edge-sanding-sequence-to-match-the-drum-sander-scratch-edger-sanding/cards/facebook/edge-sanding-sequence-to-match-the-drum-sander-scratch-edger-sanding.jpg" type="image/jpeg"/><readingTime>12</readingTime></item><item><title>Slurry Management During Wet Grinding</title><link>https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/12/03/slurry-management-during-wet-grinding-concrete-polishing/</link><guid isPermaLink="true">https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/12/03/slurry-management-during-wet-grinding-concrete-polishing/</guid><pubDate>Wed, 03 Dec 2025 13:41:04 +0000</pubDate><category>Stone &amp; Concrete Polishing</category><category>grit-40</category><category>grit-70</category><category>grit-800</category><category>grit progression</category><description>Learn expert slurry management for wet grinding and concrete polishing—chemistry, tooling, workflow, and compliance to deliver consistent, high-gloss floors.</description><summary>&lt;h2 id="wet-grinding-slurry-control-for-concrete-polishing"&gt;Wet Grinding Slurry Control for Concrete Polishing&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;It’s 6:10 a.m. in a silent warehouse. Air is cool, lights are still buzzing to full brightness, and the crew is rolling out hoses and laying edge-protection mats with the practiced choreography of a hundred previous jobs. The general contractor walks the space with a client, tracing imagined traffic patterns in the air: this will be a public lobby, high reflectivity, no coating, a breathable sheen that wears in gracefully, not off in flakes. On-site expectations like these live or die by process discipline. Everyone agrees on the end state—clean clarity, sharp aggregate reveal—but the real determinant of that result begins long before the burnish. It starts with water, abrasives, and the wet byproduct the team will generate hour after hour. It starts with slurry.&lt;/p&gt;</summary><media:content url="https://blog.equalle.com/images/brand/21.webp" medium="image"/><media:content url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/12/03/slurry-management-during-wet-grinding-concrete-polishing/cards/facebook/slurry-management-during-wet-grinding-concrete-polishing.jpg" medium="image"/><media:thumbnail url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/12/03/slurry-management-during-wet-grinding-concrete-polishing/cards/facebook/slurry-management-during-wet-grinding-concrete-polishing.jpg"/><enclosure url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/12/03/slurry-management-during-wet-grinding-concrete-polishing/cards/facebook/slurry-management-during-wet-grinding-concrete-polishing.jpg" type="image/jpeg"/><media:content url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/12/03/slurry-management-during-wet-grinding-concrete-polishing/cards/instagram/slurry-management-during-wet-grinding-concrete-polishing.jpg" medium="image"/><media:thumbnail url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/12/03/slurry-management-during-wet-grinding-concrete-polishing/cards/instagram/slurry-management-during-wet-grinding-concrete-polishing.jpg"/><enclosure url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/12/03/slurry-management-during-wet-grinding-concrete-polishing/cards/instagram/slurry-management-during-wet-grinding-concrete-polishing.jpg" type="image/jpeg"/><media:content url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/12/03/slurry-management-during-wet-grinding-concrete-polishing/cards/pinterest/slurry-management-during-wet-grinding-concrete-polishing.jpg" medium="image"/><media:thumbnail url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/12/03/slurry-management-during-wet-grinding-concrete-polishing/cards/pinterest/slurry-management-during-wet-grinding-concrete-polishing.jpg"/><enclosure url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/12/03/slurry-management-during-wet-grinding-concrete-polishing/cards/pinterest/slurry-management-during-wet-grinding-concrete-polishing.jpg" type="image/jpeg"/><media:content url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/12/03/slurry-management-during-wet-grinding-concrete-polishing/cards/facebook/slurry-management-during-wet-grinding-concrete-polishing.jpg" medium="image"/><media:thumbnail url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/12/03/slurry-management-during-wet-grinding-concrete-polishing/cards/facebook/slurry-management-during-wet-grinding-concrete-polishing.jpg"/><enclosure url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/12/03/slurry-management-during-wet-grinding-concrete-polishing/cards/facebook/slurry-management-during-wet-grinding-concrete-polishing.jpg" type="image/jpeg"/><readingTime>11</readingTime></item><item><title>How To Use A Drum Sander Without Gouging The Floor</title><link>https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/11/22/how-to-use-a-drum-sander-without-gouging-the-floor-drum-sander/</link><guid isPermaLink="true">https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/11/22/how-to-use-a-drum-sander-without-gouging-the-floor-drum-sander/</guid><pubDate>Sat, 22 Nov 2025 00:17:02 +0000</pubDate><category>Floor &amp; Deck Sanding</category><category>grit-40</category><category>grit-80</category><category>grit-100</category><category>grit-120</category><category>grit-150</category><category>dust control</category><category>dry sanding</category><category>orbital sander</category><description>Learn how to use a drum sander safely and smoothly to refinish hardwood floors without gouges, from setup and technique to edges, dust, and final prep.</description><summary>&lt;h2 id="how-to-use-a-drum-sander-without-gouging-floors"&gt;How to Use a Drum Sander Without Gouging Floors&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;There’s a specific quiet that fills the house once the furniture is moved and the rugs are rolled away. You stand in that new emptiness and see every scuff and dent that daily life has pressed into your hardwood—sun-faded planks by the windows, chair-leg tracks under the table, and a dark, worn path that arcs toward the kitchen. Maybe you’ve watched a few videos and read some forum threads, and now the rental center’s phone number is staring you down. The idea of a sparkling new finish is thrilling. The idea of gouging the floor with a poorly handled drum sander? Not so much.&lt;/p&gt;</summary><media:content url="https://blog.equalle.com/images/brand/29.webp" medium="image"/><media:content url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/11/22/how-to-use-a-drum-sander-without-gouging-the-floor-drum-sander/cards/facebook/how-to-use-a-drum-sander-without-gouging-the-floor-drum-sander.jpg" medium="image"/><media:thumbnail url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/11/22/how-to-use-a-drum-sander-without-gouging-the-floor-drum-sander/cards/facebook/how-to-use-a-drum-sander-without-gouging-the-floor-drum-sander.jpg"/><enclosure url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/11/22/how-to-use-a-drum-sander-without-gouging-the-floor-drum-sander/cards/facebook/how-to-use-a-drum-sander-without-gouging-the-floor-drum-sander.jpg" type="image/jpeg"/><media:content url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/11/22/how-to-use-a-drum-sander-without-gouging-the-floor-drum-sander/cards/instagram/how-to-use-a-drum-sander-without-gouging-the-floor-drum-sander.jpg" medium="image"/><media:thumbnail url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/11/22/how-to-use-a-drum-sander-without-gouging-the-floor-drum-sander/cards/instagram/how-to-use-a-drum-sander-without-gouging-the-floor-drum-sander.jpg"/><enclosure url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/11/22/how-to-use-a-drum-sander-without-gouging-the-floor-drum-sander/cards/instagram/how-to-use-a-drum-sander-without-gouging-the-floor-drum-sander.jpg" type="